               <persName id="t18250915-271-defend1367" type="defendantName">
                  JAMES 
                  CARTER
               <interp inst="t18250915-271-defend1367" type="surname" value="CARTER"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18250915-271-defend1367" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18250915-271-defend1367" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             was indicted, for <rs id="t18250915-271-off1456" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18250915-271-off1456" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18250915-271-off1456" type="offenceSubcategory" value="receiving"></interp>
               feloniously receiving the same, well knowing them to have been stolen
            </rs>.</p>
               <p>THOMAS JAMES REAR. I am a <rs id="t18250915-271-viclabel1457" type="occupation">chemist and druggist</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18250915-271-victim1366 t18250915-271-viclabel1457"></join>, and live in <placeName id="t18250915-271-crimeloc1458">Sloane-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18250915-271-crimeloc1458" type="placeName" value="Sloane-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18250915-271-crimeloc1458" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18250915-271-off1454 t18250915-271-crimeloc1458"></join>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18250915-271-off1456 t18250915-271-crimeloc1458"></join>. I was in my shop, about nine o'clock in the evening, on the ninth of September; the prisoners and several other persons were there; they left the shop, and I missed some bottles; Gilbert, and my apprentice, were the only persons there then - I had been shewing them to a lady about eight o'clock.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18250915-271-person1368">
                  GEORGE 
                  VAUGHAN
               <interp inst="t18250915-271-person1368" type="surname" value="VAUGHAN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18250915-271-person1368" type="given" value="GEORGE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18250915-271-person1368" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am apprentice to Mr. Rear. On the 9th of September, I saw Chapman in my master's shop; he asked for a penny-worth of liquorice, with which I served him, and he went away. I did not miss any thing till Mr. Rear told me of it.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined. Q. Were not several other persons there? A. Yes; the prisoners were the last persons who left the shop, and five minutes after they were gone, I heard of the loss.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18250915-271-person1369">
                  JAMES 
                  GILBERT
               <interp inst="t18250915-271-person1369" type="surname" value="GILBERT"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18250915-271-person1369" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18250915-271-person1369" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a musician in the Blues. On the night of the 9th of September, I was in the shop, and saw the prisoner Chapman come in.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18250915-271-person1370">
                  EDWARD 
                  PERKINS
               <interp inst="t18250915-271-person1370" type="surname" value="PERKINS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18250915-271-person1370" type="given" value="EDWARD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18250915-271-person1370" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am assistant to Mr. Perkins, a pawnbroker. On the morning of the 10th of September, Carter came to the shop, and offered these two bottles in pawn; he said, he brought them from a man. I detained him.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined. Q. Did he not go out to look for the person? A. Yes; he soon returned, and said, he was gone.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18250915-271-person1371">
                  RICHARD 
                  MAYBANK
               <interp inst="t18250915-271-person1371" type="surname" value="MAYBANK"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18250915-271-person1371" type="given" value="RICHARD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18250915-271-person1371" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am the officer - I went to Perkins' shop, and took Carter. He said they were given to him by a short man, and he was waiting for him - he did not know his name; I afterwards took Chapman from information. He said, he had not been at Mr. Rear's shop - but the apprentice and Gilbert, identified him.</p>
               <p>CARTER'S Defence. As I was coming out of the Coach and Horses public-house, I met a man at the corner of George-street, who asked me to take them to pawn, and he would give me a pint of beer.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18250915-271-person1372">
                  JOHN 
                  LONG
               <interp inst="t18250915-271-person1372" type="surname" value="LONG"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18250915-271-person1372" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18250915-271-person1372" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a labourer, and live at Chelsea. I have known Carter seven or eight years. I was at the pawnbroker's shop and saw him there - he asked for his ticket - they sent him to find the man; he returned in about a minute, and could not find him.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18250915-271-verdict1459" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18250915-271-verdict1459" type="verdictCategory" value="notGuilty"></interp>
               NOT GUILTY
            </rs>.</p>
